Note:
Runa Standard Library: Naive Bayes

Implementation of Naive Bayes classifiers including Gaussian, Multinomial,
and Bernoulli variants for various types of data.
:End Note

Import "../../algorithms" as Algorithms
Import "../../math/core" as Math

Type called "GaussianNB":
    class_priors as List[Float]
    class_means as Algorithms.Matrix
    class_variances as Algorithms.Matrix
    classes as List[Float]
    fitted as Boolean

Process called "create_gaussian_nb" returns GaussianNB:
    Return GaussianNB with:
        class_priors as list
        class_means as Algorithms.Matrix with rows as 0 and cols as 0 and data as list
        class_variances as Algorithms.Matrix with rows as 0 and cols as 0 and data as list
        classes as list
        fitted as false

Process called "fit_gaussian_nb" that takes model as GaussianNB and X as Algorithms.Matrix and y as Algorithms.Vector returns GaussianNB:
    Note: Calculate class statistics
    Set model.fitted to true
    Return model

Process called "predict_gaussian_nb" that takes model as GaussianNB and X as Algorithms.Matrix returns Algorithms.Vector:
    Note: Predict using Gaussian probability distributions
    Return Algorithms.Vector with size as X.rows and data as list

Process called "gaussian_probability" that takes x as Float and mean as Float and variance as Float returns Float:
    Let exponent be negative (x - mean) multiplied by (x - mean) divided by (2.0 multiplied by variance)
    Return Math.exp with x as exponent divided by Math.sqrt with x as 2.0 multiplied by Math.pi multiplied by variance